<subSubSection id="C36A8DB4FF80FFA5FF48FED9FF3B0DF2" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BCFDE3FFF80FFA5FF48FED9FF2E0D3A" blockId="37.[162,779,357,808]" pageId="37" pageNumber="482">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF80FFA5FF48FED9FED40F67" box="[162,263,357,378]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="482">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C70A5BCFF80FFA5FEFEFED9FE450F67" authorityName="HENDERSON" authorityYear="1888" box="[276,406,357,378]" class="Malacostraca" family="Chirostylidae" genus="Uroptychus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF80FFA5FEFEFED9FE450F67" box="[276,406,357,378]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="482">Uroptychus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a deep-sea genus of chirostylids now known to be widely distributed in Atlantic and Pacific deep reef areas. The original report (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF80FFA5FD46FE1EFEC10FCA" author="Henderson JR" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" pagination="1 - 221" refId="ref67661" refString="Henderson JR. 1888. Report on the Anomura collected by H. M. S. ' Challenger' during the years 1873 - 1876 (LXIX) 26: 1 - 221." type="journal article" year="1888">Henderson, 1888</bibRefCitation>
) was based on specimens collected during the 
<emphasis id="B904022DFF80FFA5FF39FE63FE060FE9" box="[211,469,479,500]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="482">Challenger Expedition</emphasis>
, with specimens collected from 15–734 fathoms (up to 
<quantity id="4C8873DAFF80FFA5FE11FE42FD810C0E" box="[507,594,510,531]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.398" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" unit="m" value="1398.0">1398 m</quantity>
). Shortly afterwards, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF80FFA5FF18FDA1FE770C2E" author="Benedict JE" box="[242,420,541,563]" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" pagination="243 - 344" refId="ref61225" refString="Benedict JE. 1902. Descriptions of a new genus and forty-six new species of crustaceans of the family Galatheidae, with a list of the known marine species. Proceedings of the United States National Museum 26: 243 - 344." type="journal article" year="1902">Benedict (1902)</bibRefCitation>
reported material from slightly greater depths of 163–805 fathoms (
<quantity id="4C8873DAFF80FFA5FDD4FD87FD1F0C4C" box="[574,716,571,593]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.215" metricValueMax="15.33" metricValueMin="3.1" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" unit="m" value="921.5" valueMax="1533.0" valueMin="310.0">310–1533 m</quantity>
). The genus was reported from hydrothermal vents for the first time by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF80FFA5FEA9FDC5FD180C92" author="Baba K &amp; de Saint Laurent M" box="[323,715,633,655]" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" pagination="321 - 332" refId="ref60789" refString="Baba K, de Saint Laurent M. 1992. Chirostylid and galatheid crustaceans (Decapoda: Anomura) from active thermal vent areas in the southwest Pacific. Scientia Marina 56: 321 - 332." type="journal article" year="1992">Baba &amp; de Saint Laurent (1992)</bibRefCitation>
, who described two new species from the North 
<collectingCountry id="F3679EAFFF80FFA5FD7EFD2BFD6E0CB0" box="[660,701,663,685]" name="Fiji" pageId="37" pageNumber="482">Fiji</collectingCountry>
basin. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF80FFA5FF48FD0AFE6C0CD1" author="Baba K &amp; Williams AB" box="[162,447,694,716]" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" pagination="143 - 156" refId="ref60899" refString="Baba K, Williams AB. 1998. New Galatheoidea (Crustacea, Decapoda, Anomura) from hydrothermal systems in the West Pacific Ocean: Bismarck Archipelago and Okinawa Trough. Zoosystema 20 (2): 143 - 156." type="journal article" year="1998">Baba &amp; Williams (1998)</bibRefCitation>
added a third vent species. The relatively recent descriptions of these three ventassociated species have extended the depth range to 
<quantity id="4C8873DAFF80FFA5FF48FCAEFF2A0D3A" box="[162,249,786,808]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" unit="m" value="2750.0">2750 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCFDE3FFF80FFA5FF48FCFCFF3B0DF2" blockId="37.[162,778,832,1007]" pageId="37" pageNumber="482">
<taxonomicName id="4C70A5BCFF80FFA5FF48FCFCFE9E0D48" box="[162,333,832,853]" class="Malacostraca" family="Chirostylidae" genus="Uroptychus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF80FFA5FF48FCFCFEF60D48" box="[162,293,832,853]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="482">Uroptychus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE1A3CEFF80FFA5FEB3FCFCFF390D68" author="Tunnicliffe V &amp; McArthur AG &amp; McHugh D" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" pagination="351 - 442" refId="ref78458" refString="Tunnicliffe V, McArthur AG, McHugh D. 1998. A biogeographical perspective of the deep-sea hydrothermal vent fauna. Advances in Marine Biology 34: 351 - 442." type="journal article" year="1998">Tunnicliffe, McArthur &amp; McHugh (1998)</bibRefCitation>
noted a species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C70A5BCFF80FFA5FE26FCE3FD9D0D69" authorityName="HENDERSON" authorityYear="1888" box="[460,590,863,884]" class="Malacostraca" family="Chirostylidae" genus="Uroptychus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="37" pageNumber="482" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B904022DFF80FFA5FE26FCE3FD9D0D69" box="[460,590,863,884]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="482">Uroptychus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the North 
<collectingCountry id="F3679EAFFF80FFA5FF48FCC1FF1A0D8E" box="[162,201,893,915]" name="Fiji" pageId="37" pageNumber="482">Fiji</collectingCountry>
and Lau basins. It is not yet clear whether these represent records of an undescribed species or additional sightings of one of the known species listed below.
</paragraph>
